content.description: Fun route with lots of side pulling action. Crux after the 4th bolt. Anchors are just above and to the right of the large prickly pear.
content.location: South facing wall with a small prickly pear cactus to the right, where the wall meets the ground. Finishes above and to the right of the large prickly pear.

content.description: Lots of stemming up a layered crack on an inside corner between Francis and Two Pricks. Continue past old anchor point, above small ledge where one bolt plate was removed, to anchors above larger overhang.
content.protection: Approx 6 QD's to steel loop anchors
content.location: Second route to the left, left of Francis in the corner.

content.description: Start up through or over chimney 10-15 feet to first bolt. Try not to tear any limbs off the struggling sapling as you work the rail up and around the roof.
content.protection: Approx 8 QD's to steel loop anchors.
content.location: Around the corner to the left from two pricks with the larger roof.

content.description: Someone removed the first two bolt plates, hopefully because they were damaged or shot up.
content.location: Where Jose and Juan Sisneros subtley carved their names into the wall, which is Conveniently located above a sharp corner Rock.

content.description: Wade Wall is the West-facing wall of Northeast corner of the canyon.
